  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        Let <m>A, B</m> be two subsets in a topological space <m>X</m>.
        What can you say about the relationships between
        <m>\Int(A\cap B), \Int(A\cup B)</m> and <m>\Int(A)\cap \Int(B), \Int(A)\cup \Int(B)</m>,
